# Copy to .env and adjust. All paths should point outside the repo for real data.
# Defaults (if unset) resolve under: $HOME/data/origenlab-email/
#
# GitHub: commit neither this file’s secrets nor .env. Real SQLite/PST/mbox are
# in .gitignore; clone the repo, then cp .env.example .env and set paths locally.

# Optional: single root for raw_pst, mbox, sqlite, jsonl subdirs
# ORIGENLAB_DATA_ROOT=/home/you/data/origenlab-email

# PST input directory (readpst reads from here)
# ORIGENLAB_RAW_PST_DIR=/home/you/data/origenlab-email/raw_pst

# Mbox output (01_convert_pst) and input (02_mbox_to_sqlite)
# ORIGENLAB_MBOX_DIR=/home/you/data/origenlab-email/mbox

# SQLite database path
# ORIGENLAB_SQLITE_PATH=/home/you/data/origenlab-email/sqlite/emails.sqlite

# --- PostgreSQL (OPTIONAL — not required for daily outbound or Streamlit) ---
# Operational source of truth remains SQLite (ORIGENLAB_SQLITE_PATH above). Postgres is only for:
#   - Alembic schema upgrades (uv sync --group postgres; see docs/RUNBOOK.md#m-eprun-postgres-optional)
#   - Optional SQLite→Postgres loaders under scripts/migrate/ (break-glass: can TRUNCATE/DELETE target tables)
#   - Optional outbound audit rows when you pass --write-postgres-audit on specific CLIs (see RUNBOOK)
#
# URL env vars (do not commit real passwords; use local .env only):
#   ALEMBIC_DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://user:pass@host:5432/dbname
#   ORIGENLAB_POSTGRES_URL=postgresql+psycopg://user:pass@host:5432/dbname
#
# Discovery order is NOT the same for every tool — read RUNBOOK § «Optional PostgreSQL» before setting these.
# Alembic (alembic/env.py): first non-empty of ALEMBIC_DATABASE_URL, then ORIGENLAB_POSTGRES_URL.
# Migrate scripts + optional outbound audit: CLI --postgres-url if passed, else ORIGENLAB_POSTGRES_URL, else ALEMBIC_DATABASE_URL.

# Optional Streamlit sidebar «API preview» (read-only GET; SQLite remains primary).
# Preferred: apps/api mirror on :8001 (paths under /mirror/* when base is not :8000).
# ORIGENLAB_API_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8001
# Legacy Slice-1 API (deprecated during API-3 cutover):
# ORIGENLAB_API_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000
#
# First-time Postgres migration: validate SQLite (scripts/qa/validate_sqlite_archive_for_postgres.py), then exercise
# migrate scripts only against a scratch/disposable Postgres database until counts and cutover steps are trusted.

# --- Google Workspace / Gmail IMAP (OAuth2) — PRIMARY operational mailbox path ---
# Live contacto@ (and similar) on Workspace: use this path. Rows use source_file like
# gmail:contacto@origenlab.cl/... — required for Streamlit “Actividad contacto Gmail”,
# “Casos para revisar”, and Gmail-sourced “Borrador comercial” (see docs/RUNBOOK.md).
# Full guide: docs/ingest/WORKSPACE_GMAIL_IMAP.md — uv sync --group workspace (and dev as needed).
# OAuth CLIENT json = download ONCE from Cloud Console (Desktop OAuth client).
# TOKEN json = created AUTOMATICALLY on first ingest run (browser); do not download.
# ORIGENLAB_GMAIL_OAUTH_CLIENT_JSON=/home/you/secrets/google-oauth-desktop.json
# ORIGENLAB_GMAIL_WORKSPACE_USER=contacto@origenlab.cl
# ORIGENLAB_GMAIL_TOKEN_JSON=/home/you/data/origenlab-email/secrets/gmail_workspace_token.json
# WSL: if auto-open fails (gio), set false and paste the printed URL in your browser.
# ORIGENLAB_GMAIL_OAUTH_OPEN_BROWSER=false

# --- Titan / generic IMAP (password) — legacy or optional alternate host ---
# See docs/ingest/IMAP_CONTACTO.md. Rows use imap:... source_file; Streamlit contacto review
# pages that filter gmail:contacto@... do not include these unless you also ingest via Gmail above.
# ORIGENLAB_IMAP_HOST=imap.titan.email
# ORIGENLAB_IMAP_PORT=993
# ORIGENLAB_IMAP_USER=contacto@origenlab.cl
# ORIGENLAB_IMAP_PASSWORD=...   # never commit; enable “external app” IMAP in Titan if needed

# JSONL export path
# ORIGENLAB_JSONL_PATH=/home/you/data/origenlab-email/jsonl/emails.jsonl

# Voice cohort sender domains (default: config/voice_sender_domains.txt → labdelivery.cl).
# ORIGENLAB_VOICE_SENDER_DOMAINS=labdelivery.cl,origenlab.cl
# Optional file: ORIGENLAB_VOICE_SENDER_DOMAINS_FILE=/path/to/domains.txt
#
# Optional address allowlist (scripts/dataset/*). Optional if domains file suffices.
# apps/email-pipeline/config/tatiana_senders.local.txt (gitignored; see tatiana_senders.example.txt).
# Comma-separated addresses:
# ORIGENLAB_TATIANA_SENDERS=tatiana.vivanco@origenlab.cl
# Or UTF-8 file, one address per line (# comments ok):
# ORIGENLAB_TATIANA_SENDERS_FILE=/home/you/config/tatiana_senders.local.txt

# Client reports (HTML + JSON); each run creates a subfolder YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS
# ORIGENLAB_REPORTS_DIR=/home/you/data/origenlab-email/reports

# --- Tatiana drafting copilot (OpenAI Chat; optional) ---
# Used when: uv run python scripts/tatiana/generate_tatiana_draft_package.py --generator openai_chat
# For OrigenLab drafting (same profile/context as Streamlit Borrador + pilot --origenlab-mode): add --origenlab
# Or: run_tatiana_draft_eval.py --generator openai_chat
# Prefer repo-specific key name; OPENAI_API_KEY is also accepted if unset.
# ORIGENLAB_TATIANA_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# ORIGENLAB_TATIANA_OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# Optional proxy / Azure-style base URL:
# ORIGENLAB_TATIANA_OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# ORIGENLAB_TATIANA_OPENAI_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=60
# ORIGENLAB_TATIANA_LLM_MIN_BODY_CHARS=40
# ORIGENLAB_TATIANA_LLM_ABSTAIN_ON_EMPTY_RETRIEVAL=true

# --- Docker (Streamlit business mart only) ---
# The image sets ORIGENLAB_DATA_ROOT=/data/origenlab-email. On the host, mount your
# data tree there (see README + docs/RUNBOOK.md#m-eprun-docker-streamlit).
# docker-compose.yml uses ORIGENLAB_HOST_DATA_ROOT (host path) for the bind mount.
# Do not bake secrets into the image; pass -e or an env file with container paths.
